1. Create an alert when disk usage is above 80 %
   a. create an "alert.yml" file and copy it's content from the docs
   b. edit the example to include your expression
   c. add this file to the rules_files section in prometheus.yml
   d. mount this file to your container
2. use fallocate tool to create a very big file to trigger this alarm

1. Install and configure alert manager as a docker container
2. edit prometheus configuration ( add the alert manager to it )
3. create docker compose file for both 
4. create a depencey between them 
5. read about timeseried database in the docs and presist it, same for alert manager
see: https://prometheus.io/docs/prometheus/latest/installation/#volumes--bind-mount

6. copy any exmaple of alert manager config and update it to fire two notifications
  a. telegram notificatoin 
  b. mail notification

